# Global Styling System

Workstream for site-wide design tokens, Tailwind setup, and `styles/global.css`.

## Scope

- **Global only**: typography scale, color palette, spacing, radii, shadows, base resets, and shared utility patterns live in `styles/global.css` and `tailwind.config.js`.
- **Page-specific**: layout and section styling belong in `styles/homepage.css`, `styles/projects.css`, etc. — import or extend globals, do not duplicate tokens.

## Stack

- HTML pages link `styles/global.css`.
- Base tokens and reset work immediately; run Tailwind after Node/npm is available:
  - `npm install`
  - `npm run build:css` (or `npm run watch:css` while developing)

## Conventions

- Define design tokens as CSS custom properties on `:root` in `global.css`, then map them in `tailwind.config.js` `theme.extend` where useful.
- Prefer semantic token names (`--color-text-primary`, `--font-display`) over raw values in components and page CSS.
- Keep `components/` markup free of inline styles; use Tailwind classes backed by the token system.

## Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `styles/global.css` | Tailwind layers + `:root` tokens + base element styles |
| `tailwind.config.js` | Content paths, theme extensions tied to tokens |
| `styles/*.css` (other) | Page-level overrides only |
